	@note If this message name was not handled by this control pass null into send.

raw.name: Websom.Module

members.name: baseConfig
doc: Content of moduleName.json file at module root

members.name: name
doc: Display name of module

members.name: id
doc: Unique id for this module (typically just the name of the module)

members.name: root
doc: Absolute module root directory. @note This is loaded dynamically by the module service.

members.name: @construct
doc: Base constructor that should not be overridden(use spawn instead)

members.name: registerWithServer
doc: Used by standards to bind themselves to the standard server props. e.g. Websom.Server.userSystem

members.name: clientData
doc: This is used to send(string key, primitive value) client data every route request. Access this data on the client via Websom.Client[key]

members.name: spawn
doc: Called as soon as the module is constructed(in Websom.Services.Module.start/reload). This method is not safe as other utils and services may not be initialized yet.

members.name: start
doc: Called after the server has started(before listening) services and utils. @note If you need to access another module after the start cycle use Websom.Module.loaded

members.name: stop
doc: Called when the modules are reloading, use this to clean up any resources. @warn Other modules may have stopped already, so they will be lost to the module service.

members.name: pullFromGlobalScope
doc: Only used in node environments to grab classes defined within this module.

members.name: role
doc: admin, author, moderator

members.name: connected
doc: Is this account's authentication passed onto an external OAuth system. e.g. Google, Facebook ...

members.name: locked
doc: If locked, login is not allowed.

members.name: location
doc: Usually left blank if no ip tracking service is installed.

members.name: success
doc: Did the user login.

members.name: flagged
doc: Is this login attempt or password suspicious. You should keep a calculated counting field grouped on user for mitigating brute force attacks.

members.name: service
doc: kebab-case service name. e.g. google, facebook. All lower case.
